# Project Scaffold — Design System Setup

When the user asks to start or scaffold a new project using the design system, follow these steps exactly.

## Step 1: Create Folder Structure

Create the following directory structure:

```
styles/
  tokens/
    base.css              # Base design system tokens (from Figma — read-only)
    base-components.css   # Component-specific tokens (from Figma — read-only)
    overrides.css         # Project-specific token overrides
  base/                   # Base component styles matching Figma design system
    index.css
  custom/                 # Project-specific new components
    index.css
  main.css                # Entry point — controls import order
components/
  base/                   # Base components matching Figma design system
  custom/                 # Project-specific components
```

## Step 2: Create `styles/main.css`

The import order is critical — later files override earlier ones:

```css
@import 'tokens/base.css';
@import 'tokens/base-components.css';
@import 'tokens/overrides.css';
@import 'base/index.css';
@import 'custom/index.css';
```

## Step 3: Create `styles/tokens/base.css`

Populate with ALL token values from `DESIGN_SYSTEM.md`. This includes:

- Primitive color ramps (gray, brand, error, warning, success)
- Semantic color tokens (backgrounds, text, foreground, borders, effects)
- Typography tokens (font families, weights, sizes, line heights)
- Spacing scale (none through 11xl)
- Border radius scale (none through full)
- Width and container tokens
- Shadow elevation tokens (xs through 3xl)
- Backdrop blur tokens
- Dark mode token overrides inside `.dark { }` selector

Also add `@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark)` as a fallback.

**This file is READ-ONLY after creation. Never modify it for project-specific changes.**

## Step 4: Create `styles/tokens/base-components.css`

Create an empty file with a comment header:

```css
/* Component-specific tokens from the base design system.
   Generated from Figma — do not edit manually.
   Override in overrides.css instead. */
```

## Step 5: Create `styles/tokens/overrides.css`

Create with a template showing how to override:

```css
/* Project-Specific Token Overrides
   ================================
   Override base design system tokens here.
   Never modify base.css or base-components.css directly.

   Common overrides:
   - Brand colors: override --brand-25 through --brand-950
   - Font family: override --font-family-display and --font-family-body
   - Specific semantic tokens: override --color-bg-*, --color-text-*, etc.
*/

:root {
  /* Add project-specific overrides below */
}

.dark {
  /* Add dark mode overrides for any custom tokens */
}
```

## Step 6: Create Empty Index Files

**`styles/base/index.css`:**
```css
/* Base component styles
   Import each base component stylesheet here.
   Example: @import 'button.css'; */
```

**`styles/custom/index.css`:**
```css
/* Custom project-specific component styles
   Import each custom component stylesheet here.
   Example: @import 'dashboard-card.css'; */
```

## Step 7: Copy `DESIGN_SYSTEM.md` to Project Root

If `DESIGN_SYSTEM.md` is not already in the project root, inform the user to copy it from the design-system-tokens repo. This file is the AI's primary reference for token values and conventions.

## Step 8: Verify Setup

After scaffolding, confirm:
- [ ] All directories exist
- [ ] `main.css` has correct import order
- [ ] `base.css` has all token values populated
- [ ] `overrides.css` has the template structure
- [ ] `DESIGN_SYSTEM.md` is in the project root
- [ ] Both `index.css` files exist in `base/` and `custom/`

Report what was created and remind the user:
- "base.css is read-only — all customizations go in overrides.css"
- "New components go in styles/custom/ and components/custom/"
- "Always use token variables, never hardcode values"
